          "rich_text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "WHY: Library/progress read paths are strong but the write side is under-tested and client gates are inconsistent (vocabulary delete has no client gate at all), and progress data-isolation gates are untested. RISK: a proxy viewer sees delete/write affordances the server rejects (bad UX + no regression guard); a profileId-honor or isViewingSelf privacy gate could regress silently. START: add the missing client gate + negative tests (mirror saved.test.tsx) for vocabulary/book/topic writes, and cover the three progress/index data-isolation gates.",
